    <h4>bundle update and install</h4>
    <p><code>$bundle install</code> will install gems specified in the gemfile not yet installed. <code>$bundle update</code> will install gems specified in the gemfile not yet installed, and also update existing gems to their newest tiny version. ie. 1.2.1 to 1.2.5. Generally <code>$bundle install</code> is the only one necessary to run when updates are made to the gemfile. The reason being that by running <code>$bundle update</code> without specifying the specific gem to update it will update all gems which may lead to unexpected behaviour and/or breakage.
    </p>
  </div>

