    <h4>uglifier gem</h4>
    <p>It handles file compression for the asset pipeline. Specifically in the <code>\config\environments\production.rb</code> file there is the following bit of code which tells Rails to use it as the js minifier/compressor.<p>
<pre><code class="ruby">config.assets.js_compressor = :uglifier
</code></pre>
    <p>It appears to not be included in the development.rb file by default since it would slow down development time and make debugging js more difficult.</p>
    <p>
      Further details can be found at the following link:<br>
      <a href="https://github.com/lautis/uglifier" target="_blank">https://github.com/lautis/uglifier</a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="center hero-unit post">
