    <h4>Code Syntax Highlighting</h4>
    <p>Very quickly added some code syntax highlighting to the website using the highlight.js library which can be found at the following github repository:</p>
    <p><a href="https://github.com/isagalaev/highlight.js" target="_blank">https://github.com/isagalaev/highlight.js</a></p>
    <p>and the home website where a custome package can be downloaded:</p>
    <p><a href="http://softwaremaniacs.org/soft/highlight/en/download/" target="_blank">http://softwaremaniacs.org/soft/highlight/en/download/</a></p>
    <p>After downloading the package copied the js file into the <code>app/assets/javascript</code> directory and the css file I chose into the <code>app/assets/stylesheets</code> directory. The asset pipeline for Rails automatically minifies and includes the js and css files. Lastly, until I find a proper place to put the javascript to initialize the syntax highlighting I added the following script to the end of this static html page.</p>
<pre><code class="js">&lt;script&gt;
  $( document ).ready(function() {
    // process the pre code tags
    hljs.initHighlightingOnLoad();
  });
&lt;/script&gt;
</code></pre>
    <p>Now all I need to do is place my code inside of html tags like so:</p>
<pre><code class="html">&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class="js"&gt;var test = 'blah';&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
</code></pre>
  <p>To get the following syntax highlighted output:</p>
<pre><code class="js">var test = 'blah';</code></pre>

